        <text>
                <body>
                        <div type="writingSession">
                                <opener>
                                        <dateline><pb/> Octbr. 1, 66.</dateline>
                                        <salute>Dear Engels!</salute>
                                </opener>
                                <p><seg type="comment"><anchor type="verweisziel" xml:id="start_pgx_hcy_pz"/><orig>I enclose you a
                                                  Prospectus of the <bibl sameAs="ed_mzl_3hf_lbb">Mitteldeutsche Volkszeitung.</bibl></orig><note xml:id="c584406c-2078-4416-8755-c18ba9b97eef">Zu
                                                  <persName key="pdrPo.001.004.000002822">Liebknechts</persName> Absicht, eine Zeitung
                                                  herauszugeben, siehe <ref target="B00107/#e33a4f20-560e-4751-bfa6-23082a56d336">Erl. zu W. Liebknecht an Marx, zw. 8. u.
                                                  15.5.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170519T122808+0200" comment="{{Erl. 103g}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?>.</ref>
                                                  Siehe auch <ref target="B00151">W. Liebknecht an
                                                  Marx,
                                                  10.8.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170504T104004+0200" comment="{{Br. 147.2–15}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>.
                                                  Der beigelegte Prospekt der <bibl sameAs="ed_mzl_3hf_lbb">„Mitteldeutschen
                                                  Volks-Zeitung“</bibl> (Leipzig)
                                                  <!--(((zMitteldeutsche Volks-Zeitung)))--> konnte
                                                  nicht ermittelt werden.</note></seg> Originally
                                        this paper was founded 5 years ago by “honest democrats”
                                        (Confusionarii) became soon quite <seg type="comment"><orig>“Gothaic”</orig><note xml:id="a59684de-f3b7-4b37-8b1e-d579cdd4a04b">Siehe <ref target="B00116/#c0a50206-8d39-4240-add7-1df8139bd92d">Erl. zu W. Liebknecht an Marx,
                                                  25.5.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170519T123118+0200" comment="{{Erl. 112c}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?>.</ref></note></seg>,
                                        attacked us, and was attacked in return, had to be sold
                                        because we had robbed it of almost all its Abonnenten, was
                                        offered to me, bought by me (!!) and a friend as rich as I
                                        for a trifle, and handed over to a committee, out of which
                                        sprang the Share-company, that published the enclosed
                                        prospectus. <seg type="comment"><orig>For one month I edited
                                                  the paper with some success, until it was
                                                  suppressed by the Prussians four weeks
                                                  ago;</orig><note xml:id="f82e1f68-fa93-4096-97f3-15804babdd85">Die
                                                  <bibl sameAs="ed_mzl_3hf_lbb">„Mitteldeutsche
                                                  Volks-Zeitung“</bibl> (Leipzig)
                                                  <!--(((zMitteldeutsche Volks-Zeitung)))--> wurde
                                                  am 29. August 1866 von der preußischen
                                                  Stadtkommandatur für zunächst vier Wochen
                                                  verboten; siehe auch <ref target="B00107/#e33a4f20-560e-4751-bfa6-23082a56d336">Erl. zu W. Liebknecht an Marx, zw. 8. u.
                                                  15.5.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170519T122808+0200" comment="{{Erl. 103g}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>.
                                                  Sie Anfang Oktober 1866 erneut herauszugeben
                                                  scheiterte.</note></seg> and now we are waiting
                                        for the conclusion of peace, when it shall reappear
                                        again.</p>
                                <p>The “Mitteldeutsche” will be an organ of the <hi rendition="#u">International W. Ass.</hi> and <hi rendition="#u">expects</hi> articles <hi rendition="#u">from
                                                you</hi> and <seg type="comment"><orig><hi rendition="#u">Williams</hi></orig><note xml:id="dba27732-8e28-4f9b-bca2-880eec96657f">Karl
                                                  Marx.</note></seg>; and besides articles it
                                        expects some <hi rendition="#u">more substantial assistance
                                                in the form of shares</hi> and Abonnements. Please,
                                        do what you can,—the more shares and subscriptions our party
                                        takes, <pb/> the greater is my (and our) influence in the
                                        direction of the paper.</p>
                                <p>As to the Abonnements I need hardly tell you, that they have to
                                        be taken in England at the <hi rendition="#u">Post-office</hi>.</p>
                                <p>Please to send the prospectus <hi rendition="#uu">filled up</hi>
                                        to <hi rendition="#uu">me</hi>; <seg type="comment"><orig><expan>Adv<ex>okat</ex></expan>
                                                  Freytag</orig><note xml:id="c695f34b-a8ca-4725-9fba-0149bd9629c8"><persName key="ed_kft_qck_nz">Otto
                                                  Freytag</persName>. </note></seg>, mentioned in
                                        it, is overworked now, and has several cases of Cholera in
                                        his house.<anchor type="verweisziel" xml:id="stop_pgx_hcy_pz"/></p>
                                <p><seg type="comment"><orig>I am at present in Berlin (since
                                                  3 days) and shall stop till the 4<hi rendition="#sup">th</hi> inst.</orig><note xml:id="d3cd7232-86f4-4309-a619-7609ed71e384">Nach
                                                  Verkündung einer Amnestie 1866 in Preußen,
                                                  anlässlich des Sieges über Österreich, glaubte
                                                  <persName key="pdrPo.001.004.000002822">Liebknecht</persName>, seine Ausweisung aus
                                                  Preußen vom Sommer 1865 (siehe <ref target="B00011/#a4016170-75c2-4918-b14f-5981f8456429">Erl. zu Marx an W. Liebknecht,
                                                  15.1.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170519T123257+0200" comment="{{Erl. 10e}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>)
                                                  wäre hinfällig. Er war offen nach Berlin gekommen,
                                                  aber am 2. Oktober 1866 nach einer Versammlung im
                                                  Verein der Buchdruckergehilfen dort verhaftet und
                                                  am 19. Oktober zu drei Monaten Gefängnis (bis
                                                  17. Januar 1867) verurteilt worden. Siehe <bibl sameAs="zotero-604880-VGHM3M5D">Offizieller
                                                  Bericht des Königlichen Polizeipräsidiums in
                                                  Berlin</bibl> an <persName key="pdrPo.001.004.000002819">Ernestine
                                                  Liebknecht</persName> vom 15. Oktober 1866 über
                                                  die Verhaftung Liebknechts (RGASPI, Sign. f. 200,
                                                  op. 3, d. 23) und <bibl sameAs="zotero-604880-8PWCQYZM">Offizieller
                                                  Bericht des Stadtgerichts Berlin</bibl> an
                                                  Ernestine Liebknecht vom 15. Oktober 1866 über die
                                                  Verhaftung Liebknechts (IISG, Wilhelm
                                                  Liebknecht-Nachlass, Sign. 482). <!--(((lOffizieller_Bericht des Königlichen
                                                  Polizeipräsidiums in Berlin an Ernestine
                                                  Liebknecht vom 15. Oktober 1866 über die
                                                  Verhaftung Liebknechts (RGASPI, Sign. f. 200,
                                                  op. 3, d. 23) )))-->
                                                  <!--(((lOffizieller_Bericht des Stadtgerichts Berlin
                                                  an Ernestine Liebknecht vom 15. Oktober 1866
                                                  über die Verhaftung Liebknechts (IISG, Wilhelm
                                                  Liebknecht-Nachlass, Sign. 482) )))-->
                                                  Siehe <ref target="B00184/#start_ick_czb_5z">L.
                                                  Kugelmann an Marx,
                                                  11.10.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170504T110810+0200" comment="{{Br._179.37–43}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>;
                                                  <ref target="B00195/#start_uhp_xny_nz">J. Ph.
                                                  Becker an Marx,
                                                  15.11.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170504T111031+0200" comment="{{Br. 189.35–37}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>;
                                                  <ref target="B00200/#start_dms_4zb_5z">S. Meyer an
                                                  Marx,
                                                  3.12.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170504T111306+0200" comment="{{Br._193.30–36}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>
                                                  und <ref target="B00206/#start_iry_wzb_5z">Marx an
                                                  Engels,
                                                  8.12.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170504T111523+0200" comment="{{Br. 199.15–17}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>.
                                                  Siehe auch <bibl sameAs="zotero-604880-MICKEHW4">Bernstein: Geschichte der Berliner
                                                  Arbeiter-Bewegung. Teil 1.</bibl> S. 151.
                                                  <!--(((lBernstein: Geschichte der Berliner
                                                  Arbeiter-Bewegung. Teil 1.)))-->
                                                </note></seg> Amongst the working classes there is
                                        good democratic feeling, but the bourgeoisie is <hi rendition="#u">thoroughly corrupted</hi>. <seg type="comment"><orig><hi rendition="#u">Jacoby</hi></orig><note xml:id="bdec74d2-8d25-497d-8995-18a017c63ac9"><persName key="pdrPo.001.004.000002341">Johann
                                                  Jacoby</persName>. </note></seg> owned that to me
                                        yesterday, and I think he will <hi rendition="#u">quite</hi>
                                        come round to us. <hi rendition="#u"><persName key="pdrPo.001.004.000001931">Groote</persName></hi> too, who is the best of the
                                        whole lot , though a little narrow in his ideas; but full of
                                        energy and—gall.</p>
                                <p><seg type="comment"><orig>Your 5 £. note</orig><note xml:id="nqvy_1wr_3z">Über eine Zuwendung von
                                                  Engels an <persName key="pdrPo.001.004.000002822">Liebknecht</persName> gibt es keine
                                                  Anhaltspunkte. </note></seg> I had to use after
                                        all, and could have used several more if I had had them.
                                        From the moment I had to unfurl our banner here I was <pb/>
                                        systematically deprived of all sources of existence; then
                                        came <seg type="comment"><orig>the war crisis,</orig><note xml:id="d608c527-d4e6-45fd-9684-caf1784b3f09">Der
                                                  sich abzeichnende Deutsche Krieg von
                                                1866.</note></seg> and last not least the
                                        suppression of the paper, which blow took <hi rendition="#u">every farthing</hi> from me; the shares not being
                                        taken yet, and nobody having money enough to advance me my
                                        salary. From this you see that if you send some money you
                                        will oblige not only our “party” but also my own poor self,
                                        at least to some extent. (Here I am as the guest of a
                                                  <expan>manufa<ex>c</ex>turer</expan>, who took me
                                        over from Leipzig and will also pay the journey back. His
                                        name is <persName key="ed_jkt_33k_nz">Schütte</persName>, 97
                                        Ritterstr.) The money invested in shares is <hi rendition="#u">not lost</hi>; we have already <hi rendition="#uu">1500</hi> subscribers, the number
                                        was fast increasing when the paper was suppressed, and the
                                        suppression has made us only the more popular. The “Caution”
                                        of 2000 r<ex>eichstaler</ex>
                                        <hi rendition="#u">is paid</hi>. In fact the <bibl sameAs="ed_mzl_3hf_lbb">Mitteldeutsche</bibl> is not
                                        a sham but a reality, and as <hi rendition="#u">all</hi> the
                                        noteworthy democrats of Germany have promised their
                                        assistance I hope it will become worthy of the principles I
                                        shall try to advocate in it.</p>
                                <p>I am in a hurry. So excuse me.</p>
                                <closer>Your <hi rendition="#u">J. Miller, 10 Bayrische
                                                Strasse</hi><lb/><hi rendition="#u">Leipzig</hi>.</closer>
                                <closer><supplied cert="high">Ve</supplied>rte! </closer>
                                <postscript>
                                        <p><pb/>
                                                <seg type="comment"><orig>Won't you write anything
                                                  about the war?</orig><note xml:id="bf57ea93-94c8-4aa8-bd69-2e0b30d12045">Engels schrieb zu Beginn des Deutschen Krieges im
                                                  Juni/Juli 1866 die 5-teilige Artikelserie <bibl sameAs="zotero-604880-K4MA8973">„Notes on the
                                                  War“</bibl> für <bibl sameAs="ed_cms_nhf_lbb">„The
                                                  Manchester Guardian“</bibl> (<bibl sameAs="zotero-604880-3WIRUBDF">MEGA² I/20.
                                                  S. 206–223</bibl>). Siehe auch <ref target="B00125/#fea1b6e7-864d-4c78-ab8c-74c4578f26b2">Erl. zu H. Morrell Acton an Engels,
                                                  18.6.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170519T123557+0200" comment="{{Erl. 121a}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>
                                                  und <ref target="B00128/#nrl1_jnp_fz">Erl. zu Marx
                                                  an Engels,
                                                  20.6.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170519T123744+0200" comment="{{Erl._124c}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?>.</ref>
                                                  <!--(((l[Engels, Friedrich:] Notes on the war in
                                                  Germany. No. I. In: The Manchester Guardian.
                                                  Nr. 6190, 20. Juni 1866. S. 2/3;
                                                  Notes on the war in Germany. No. II. Ebenda.
                                                  Nr. 6194, 25. Juni 1866. S. 2/3;
                                                  Notes on the war. No. III. Ebenda.
                                                  Nr. 6197, 28. Juni 1866. S. 2/3;
                                                  Notes on the war. No. IV. Ebenda.
                                                  Nr. 6201, 3. Juli 1866. S. 6; Notes
                                                  on the war. No. V. Ebenda. Nr. 6204,
                                                  6. Juli 1866. S. 2/3. (MEGA² I/20.
                                                  S. 206–223.) )))--></note></seg>——When
                                                will the second Edition of <seg type="comment"><orig>your “Lage” appear?</orig><note xml:id="d84eca62-0b57-49fa-9b0e-881c61cdd394"><bibl sameAs="zotero-604880-UIFI5RLI">Friedrich
                                                  Engels: Die Lage der arbeitenden Klasse in
                                                  England. Leipzig 1845.</bibl> Die <bibl sameAs="zotero-604880-JBEA5LKR">zweite deutsche
                                                  Ausgabe</bibl> erschien erst im Jahre 1892. Siehe
                                                  auch <ref target="B00036/#ng5n_lfy_5y">Erl. zu
                                                  Marx an Engels,
                                                  10.2.<?oxy_comment_start author="reichhoff" timestamp="20170519T123953+0200" comment="{{Erl. 33d}}"?>1866<?oxy_comment_end?></ref>. <!--(((lEngels,Friedrich:Die Lage
                                                  der arbeitenden Klasse in England. Leipzig 1845)))-->
                                                  <!--(((lEngels,Friedrich:Die Lage der arbeitenden
                                                  Klasse in England. Nach eigner Anschauung und
                                                  authentischen Quellen. 2. durchges. Aufl.
                                                  Stuttgart 1892)))--></note></seg>—
                                                Could you not send me your photograph?—</p>
                                </postscript>
                        </div>
                        <div type="writingSession">
                                <p>Once more your<lb/>J. Miller<lb/>10 Bayrische
                                        Strasse<lb/>Leipzig. </p>
                        </div>
                </body>
